Azure DDoS Protection safeguards applications from Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS) attacks, which attempt to overwhelm systems with traffic.

Azure provides:

* Basic protection (default)
* Standard protection (enhanced)

For example, during a DDoS attack, Azure automatically detects and mitigates malicious traffic.

A real-life use case is an e-commerce website during a sale event, where attackers may try to disrupt services.

Another example is financial platforms that must remain accessible at all times.

DDoS protection ensures availability and resilience against cyber attacks.
